{"id":14881693,"mediaExerciseId":"8b89d6c4-4b6a-4568-b555-3803b016571d","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"19A","chapterTitle":"Determining the Target Cash Balance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":671,"solutions":[{"id":6022657,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to assess whether the mentioned changes in target cash balances will lead to its increase or decrease. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/9dd206588c78bebf9a12d45562036901/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/9dd206588c78bebf9a12d45562036901/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**a)** If broker commissions are reduced, then company costs are reduced as well. So, in this case, there is an increase in target cash balance. \n\nAnswer: I","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/5e8ee6cd3bf38df6f218e043bd4202ce/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/5e8ee6cd3bf38df6f218e043bd4202ce/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)** If interest rates on money market securities increase, then holding costs increase. Then the company's cash is reduced, which means that the companyâ€™s target cash balance is reduced. \n\nAnswer: D","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/7bc9f260211d4534a398207f53311baf/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/7bc9f260211d4534a398207f53311baf/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**c)** If a compensating balance is raised, this means that the minimum deposit that the borrower must keep in the bank account increases. However, this leads to reduced company cash, which means that the target cash balance is decreased.  \n\nAnswer: D","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":176,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/9179dbff596b65e8db6a12e8483524ed/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/9179dbff596b65e8db6a12e8483524ed/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**d)** If the credit rating of a company improves, then this may lead to the bank approving some loans to company on more favorable terms. This means that the company reduces its costs, which leads to an increase target cash balance. \n\nAnswer: I","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":176,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/b3be261338e4c28b09b3b727b6ba4432/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/b3be261338e4c28b09b3b727b6ba4432/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"**e)**  If the cost of borrowing increases, then the firm should set aside more of its available cash. This leads to a reduction of target cash balance. \n\nAnswer: D","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/28ecb447de23356f242e0e898d51b169/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/28ecb447de23356f242e0e898d51b169/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"**f)**  If fees for direct banking services are charged, then the firm should set aside money to cover those costs, which leads to a reduction of target cash balance. \n\nAnswer: D","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/dfe0886f7c11acec787e99825d7950c4/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/14/5270446de5247551cdf025fc35932960/dfe0886f7c11acec787e99825d7950c4/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"c9a2798e-d058-482e-af8a-907c6c3a64cc","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881694,"exerciseName":"2","page":671,"hasSolution":true,"m